claim.claim-text:
The safety needle of claim 4, characterized in that the needle (3, 103, 303) being hollow and having a tip (303a) for injecting into the patient and a longitudinal axis;

a hub mounted (7, 107, 307) to the needle (3, 103, 303) and having an outer surface (18, 318), a receiving end (307b) distal to the tip (303a) of the needle (303) and an injection end (307a) proximal to the tip (303a) of the needle (303), at least part of the outer surface (18, 318) of the hub (7, 107, 307) tapering toward the injection end (307a); and

a slidable (5, 105, 305) sleeve having a mounting end (305b) distal to the tip (303a) of the needle (303) and an injection end (305a) proximal to the tip (303a) of the needle (303), the tip (303a) of the needle (303) being located inside the slidable sleeve (5, 105, 305) in an extended position, the tip (303a) of the needles (303) projecting from the slidable sleeve (5, 105, 305) in a retracted position, the slidable sleeve (5, 105, 305) being slidably mounted to the hub (7, 107, 307) between the receiving and injection ends (307b, 307a) of the hub (307) in the initial position, the initial position being between the retracted and extended positions, the outer surface (18, 318) of the hub (7, 107, 307) deflecting the slidable sleeve outwardly in a radial direction as the slidable sleeve (5, 105, 305) slides axially toward the receiving end (307b) of the hub (307), and that a displacement force urges the slidable sleeve (5, 105, 305) from the initial position toward the retracted position generating a restoring force within the slidable sleeve (5, 105, 305), the restoring force urging the slidable sleeve (5, 105, 305) to move toward the injection end (307b) of the needle hub (307) and into the extended position upon removal of the displacement force.
